[32m+[m[32m# 🐍 Basic Python for Data Science – My First Steps[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mWelcome to the **Basic Python** section of my Data Science journey![m[41m  [m
[32m+[m[32mThis folder contains essential Python concepts that are important for anyone starting in data science. These are not just simple codes — they are the base for real-world tasks like data cleaning, automation, and logic building.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## 🚧 Why Start with Python Basics?[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mBefore working with data, I must understand how to:[m
[32m+[m[32m- Write clear and correct Python code[m
[32m+[m[32m- Think like a programmer (logical steps)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Use Python to solve small real-life problems[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThese skills are needed when working with tools like Pandas, NumPy, or scikit-learn later on.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## 🧠 What You'll Learn Here[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mEach file in this folder teaches a concept that is often used in real-world data tasks:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m| Topic               | Real-World Use Case Example                       |[m
[32m+[m[32m|--------------------|---------------------------------------------------|[m
[32m+[m[32m| Variables & Input  | Storing user data or values from a form          |[m
[32m+[m[32m| If-Else Logic      | Making decisions (e.g. fraud detection rules)     |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Loops              | Repeating tasks like reading many files           |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Functions          | Writing reusable steps like cleaning data         |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Strings            | Formatting reports or cleaning text data          |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Lists & Dicts      | Handling JSON, CSV rows, or API results           |[m
[32m+[m[32m| Sets & Tuples      | Unique data (like unique user IDs)                |[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## 🗂 Folder Structure[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mExample file list (you can rename yours similarly):[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- `01_variables_input.py` – collecting and storing input[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m[32m- `02_control_flow.py` – making decisions with if/else[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m[32m- `03_loops.py` – for and while loops[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m[32m- `04_functions.py` – writing reusable code blocks[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m[32m- `05_data_structures.py` – lists, dictionaries, sets, tuples[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m[32m- `06_string_operations.py` – cleaning and editing text[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m[32m- `07_basic_errors.py` – catching simple errors[m[41m  [m
[32m+[m[32m- `08_real_world_examples.py` – simple data-related problems[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## 🌍 Real Examples (Mini Projects)[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mSome files may include:[m
[32m+[m[32m- Bill calculator[m
[32m+[m[32m- Student grade checker[m
[32m+[m[32m- Simple chatbot[m
[32m+[m[32m- Basic email/text formatter[m
[32m+[m[32m- Word counter from a paragraph[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mThese are simple now but help me build skills for bigger data science tasks later.[m
